<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 23 at 12:52PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Patchy Freezing Rain and Icy Roads Possible This Afternoon...
Temperatures are still around freezing early this afternoon and
with some light and patchy showers tracking into the Mohawk Valley
and the western and southern Adirondacks, some roads, especially
elevated roads, overpasses and bridges, may turn icy. Use caution
if traveling through this afternoon.</description>
